    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 18 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO-14618 AND RTLO-16618
        SERIES - AIR SYSTEM - SLAVE VALVES
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl1301505" svcproctype="disassemble" graphiccount="1">
        <title>SLAVE VALVES</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301906">Figure 6</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f1301906" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g1301906" filename="../figg13/g1301906.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
            <caption>Figure 6. Slave Valves</caption>
        </figure>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk xrefid="f1301906">Figure 6</hotlnk>
            for disassembly and reassembly of the piston-type slave valve assemblies. Should the poppet-type slave valve
            assembly prove to be defective, replace the complete assembly, as it is non-serviceable. The actuating
            components used with these valve assemblies are non-interchangeable. Failure to use the correct plunger pin,
            spring, and alignment sleeve during installation on the transmission will cause hard shifting in LO Range
            gears.
        </para>
    </svcproc>
